Patient: What should I drink to help my heart?

Educator: Drink clean water mainly. Avoid drinks high in sugar or salt like soda.

Patient: But I like soda, why can't I have it?

Educator: Soda has lots of sugar and salt. These can make your heart work too hard.

Patient: Clean water is hard to get. What can I do?

Educator: Try boiling water or use a filter. Some community programs can help too.

Patient: Will drinking water really help my heart?

Educator: Yes, it helps your heart work less hard. And it's better than sugary or salty drinks.